{\f1\fs28\b 1. Introduction and Purpose}\par
\par
{\f0\fs20
DJs Timeline-maskin (DJs Timeline Machine) is a specialized desktop application designed specifically for investigative journalists and researchers. The application streamlines the complex process of organizing research materials, processing documents, and creating detailed timelines of events.
\par\par
{\b Key Benefits:}\par
\bullet Automates PDF file organization and renaming\par
\bullet Creates structured Excel timelines with rich text formatting\par
\bullet Preserves research data with session persistence\par
\bullet Supports collaborative research workflows\par
\bullet Maintains professional documentation standards\par
\par
{\b Primary Use Cases:}\par
\bullet Processing large volumes of PDF documents from news archives\par
\bullet Creating chronological timelines of events for investigations\par
\bullet Organizing source materials with consistent naming conventions\par
\bullet Maintaining detailed research notes with rich text formatting\par
\bullet Collaborative timeline creation for research teams\par
\par
{\b Application Workflow:}\par
The application follows a systematic 4-step process:\par
1. {\b PDF Selection} - Choose and validate PDF documents\par
2. {\b Component Editing} - Parse and edit filename components\par
3. {\b Excel Integration} - Map data to timeline fields with rich formatting\par
4. {\b Save Operations} - Rename files and update Excel timelines\par
}
