  \bullet Solution: Reinstall Python with "Add to PATH" option checked\par
  \bullet Test: Open Command Prompt, type {\f2 python --version}\par
\bullet {\b Missing dependencies}\par
  \bullet Solution: Run {\f2 pip install ttkbootstrap PyPDF2 openpyxl xlsxwriter}\par
  \bullet Test: Import each library individually in Python interpreter\par
\bullet {\b Corrupted configuration file}\par
  \bullet Solution: Delete {\f2 pdf_processor_config.json} and restart application\par
  \bullet Test: Check if JSON file contains valid syntax\par
\bullet {\b File permissions issue}\par
  \bullet Solution: Run Command Prompt as Administrator\par
  \bullet Test: Try running from different folder location\par
